<F P=106> [Article by Yu Yikuan [0151 5030 1401]: ``Fuzhou </F>
(Hangzhou)-Guilin-Chengdu Fiber Optic Cable To Be Built''] 
  [Summary] It has been learned from authoritative sources 
that construction on China's longest fiber optic cable 
communications trunk line -- the Fuzhou 
(Hangzhou)-Guilin-Chengdu cable -- will begin this year. This 
4,354-km-long, 1.071-billion-yuan trunk line will link up six 
provinces: Fujian, Zhejiang, Jiangxi, Hunan, Guizhou, and 
Sichuan. 

