<F P=106> [Article by Zheng Zhaosen [6774 0340 2773]: </F>
``808-nm-Wavelength, 980-nm-Wavelength Quantum Well Laser 
Diodes''] 
  [Summary] The 808-nm-wavelength high-power AlGaAs quantum 
well laser diode and 980-nm-wavelength InGaAs/AlGaAs 
strained-layer quantum well laser diode developed by MEI's 
Institute 13 as pump sources for solid state lasers recently 
passed design finalization. The former laser diode is a key 
device used in all-solid-state YAG lasers, while the latter is a 
key device for erbium-doped fiber optical amplifiers. Both 
achievements were listed as Eighth FYP Key State Projects and 
863 Plan key projects. 

